    },
    {
      "name": "6 · Error Cases",
      "description": "Explore validation and error responses.\n\nAll errors follow this shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 400,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2025-06-15T10:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"path\": \"/the/requested/path\",\n  \"message\": \"Human-readable error\"\n}\n```",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Employee — unknown skillId → 400",
          "description": "Sending a valid UUID that does not reference an existing skill triggers a PostgreSQL foreign-key violation (SQLSTATE 23503), which the API maps to `400 Bad Request`.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "pm.test('Message mentions referenced resource', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('Referenced resource not found'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Ghost Employee\",\n  \"skillIds\": [\"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000\"]\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/employees", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["employees"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Skill — duplicate name → 409",
          "description": "Skill names must be unique. Creating a second skill with the same name triggers a PostgreSQL unique-constraint violation (SQLSTATE 23505), which the API maps to `409 Conflict`.\n\n> **Prerequisite:** run *Create Skill — Assembly* first so the name `Assembly` already exists.",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
